name: PIGEON
summary: Various news articles related to the topic of "pigeon" have been released. An Ohio family is facing the loss of their home in Pigeon Forge due to eminent domain. King Charles III has withdrawn royal patronage from pigeon racing, causing controversy. A new steakhouse is opening across the street from a Freret Street restaurant. A journalist embarked on a "pigeon safari" to challenge their prejudice against the birds. White Pigeon Days, an annual celebration, is approaching in Sturgis. Pigeon Forge officials have provided a statement regarding the Ohio family's home acquisition. The Pigeon Forge Police are searching for a missing woman who was last seen in March. WildSide in Pigeon Forge has expanded its offerings with new mountain biking and UTV trails. A fire damaged a steel casting plant near Pigeon. Finally, an Irish animated short film titled "Póg mo Pigeon" is set to premiere at the Galway Film Fleadh.

name: The Shining
summary: Actress Shelley Duvall, known for her iconic roles in "The Shining" and "Nashville," has passed away at 75 due to complications from diabetes. Duvall's portrayal of Wendy Torrance in Stanley Kubrick's "The Shining" left an indelible mark on cinema, earning critical acclaim for her depiction of a tormented wife. However, her experience on set was reportedly challenging, and she later spoke about the emotional toll it took on her. Despite her struggles, Duvall's performance showcased her strength and vulnerability, solidifying her status as a compelling and unforgettable actress.

name: Steve Gleason
summary: Former New Orleans Saints safety Steve Gleason, who was diagnosed with amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) in 2011, received the 2024 Arthur Ashe Courage Award at the ESPY Awards for his tireless advocacy and work in raising awareness for ALS. In an emotional speech, Gleason reflected on his journey with ALS, highlighting the importance of embracing life's challenges and using one's story to inspire others. His speech was met with a standing ovation and praise from many, including fellow athletes, celebrities, and politicians.

name: Monte Kiffin
summary: The legendary football coach, Monte Kiffin, has passed away at 84. Kiffin was a key figure in American football, serving as the defensive coordinator for the New Orleans Saints in 1995 and the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, where he won Super Bowl 37. He is also well-known as the father of current Ole Miss head coach, Lane Kiffin. Monte Kiffin's contributions to football are widely recognized, with many sources, including Yahoo Sports, CBS Sports, and ESPN, commemorating his impact on the sport. His legacy as a renowned defensive coach extends beyond professional football, as he also made a significant mark in college football. The passing of Monte Kiffin is a profound loss for the football community, and his influence on the sport will continue to be felt by players and coaches alike.

name: Jamal Adams
summary: The Tennessee Titans have acquired veteran safety Jamal Adams, a three-time Pro Bowler, on a one-year contract. Adams was previously released by the Seattle Seahawks in May after four seasons with the team. He has also played for the New York Jets, who drafted him sixth overall in the 2017 NFL Draft. Adams has been named to the Pro Bowl in each of the past three seasons, and he was also a First-Team All-Pro selection in 2019. The Titans are hoping that Adams can help improve their defense, which ranked 21st in the NFL in passing yards allowed in 2022.
